{
  "stem": "11722.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And he had this little bag of food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And by that time my mother and my little brothers and my sister and my aunt and my cousins went to the right.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And my father told my brother to take over the food stuff to my mother because we didn't know how long before we'll see one another again.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And they wouldn't let my little brother back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And then all these people who were on the right, they marched them off to this building.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I remember there was some stench in the air.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "There was a big chimney.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We didn't know anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And we know now these people were marched to these buildings.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "They were asked to undress, to put their clothes neatly, and they were [GERMAN], disinfection.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And they were ushered into this room where there were looked like showers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Now we know instead of showers they turned on these Zyklon B gas faucets and they gassed these poor souls.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] That's the kind of death my family met.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] After that the Sonderkommando [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] went in there after they aired out with gas masks.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "They unhooked these bodies.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Even in death you could tell family, family members.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I went back in 1990 with fellow survivors with mixed emotions [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] to pay my respect to my family.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I have no grave site.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And I remember these bombed out crematoriums.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "The Nazis bombed them out because they didn't want to leave any traces of evidence.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "I remember they had this guide tell tourists that Auschwitz, Birkenau, had the capacity of gassing [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] 20,000 people a day, and burning in the crematorium 10,000 people a day.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
